RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED WINE TIME , reluctant to load, hesitated at the break spotting the field about three lengths, found herself far back of the embattled pair up front, was under strong ride gathering steam leaving the far turn, circled five wide into the stretch, shifted out wider past the three sixteenths, made a grinding run under left handed asks and on her left lead and forged ahead in the final yards. WATER WITCH , outrun early while saving ground, was put to strong urging past the five eighths, gained towards the rail past the five sixteenths, swung out five wide soon into the lane, rallied outside to collar the leader near the sixteenth pole, gained a short lead between runners soon after, kept on gamely but just could not hold off the winner's charge. RATIONALMILLENNIAL tracked the dueling leaders while saving ground, eased out nearing the far turn, bid three wide outside HEARDITALL nearing the three eighths, sparred outside that one to the quarter pole, was shoved clear in upper stretch, dug in when engaged approaching the sixteenth pole then gave way grudgingly. ALWAJD stalked early outside a rival, was under a serious ride mid way on the final turn, dropped inside for the drive but came up empty. BAD TEMPER set a pressured pace towards the rail, was headed five furlongs out, stayed on into the far turn, eased out with pursuit near the five sixteenths and gave way. HEARDITALL rushed up early to join BAD TEMPER, pressed outside that one before putting a head in front near the five eighths, was engaged from her outside leaving the far turn, battled to the inside of RATIONALMILLENIAL to the quarter pole then gave way. SHE SO COOL , well placed in the clear mid way through the backstretch run, had no response into the far turn and faltered.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROMP rated forwardly outside rivals, edged closer under some coaxing leaving the far turn, bid three deep approaching the quarter pole, gained a slim advantage dueling outside CHELONIAN leaving the three sixteenths, kept on under right handed asks soon after, had his rider put the stick away for the final furlong and dug in tenaciously under a solid hand ride to preserve the score. CHELONIAN prompted the pace two wide outside PHRA PHROM, moved alongside near the three eighths, battled between foes leaving the five sixteenths, emerged in a battle to the inside of the winner in upper stretch, fought valiantly from there and was able to save the place. DOWN COLD steadied off heels nearing the backstretch, shifted out and stalked between runners, dropped back after steadying near the three furlong marker, regrouped to advance between runners into the stretch, angled out and came back on with good energy to gain. THE ADDISON POUR broke a step slow, steadied off heels while wide into the backstretch, remained wide into the far turn, was floated out near the three eighths and came up empty through the lane. PHRA PHROM took over between runners into the first turn, dropped in and set the pace, held a clear lead past the five eighths, dug in when joined by CHELONIAN exiting the far turn, sparred to the head of the lane then gave way. GOLDEN PEGASUS checked off the leader's heels approaching the backstretch, regrouped to track towards the rail, lost his rider when sustaining a catastrophic injury leaving the far turn then was euthanized on the track. There was a stewards' inquiry. No action was taken.
